ive been contemplating writing this, because this going to sound a bit "sussy" but just try to understand it from my point, but i main medic 99% of the time, as well as others who just do nothing but go medic. and theres a handful of people that will go medic and help the team out and not be a player who picks up a medkit and med ammo and not using it that i can trust just because they simply know what theyre doing, I understand what im about to say is 'a part of the game and is bound to happen' but im trying to reduce the amount of this happening. today on powercliff when C was falling, i teleported to find Engy, Liver and 2 other s outside in the sewer, they were all low and naturally i threw a medbomb out into the sewers to heals them and tried to evaluate who had the lowest HP. Liver had 40, one guy had 30, and a level 12 had 3 hp, so out of instinct i healed the level 12, and liver ended up dying, and i felt bad, because the level 12 turned around after 1 heal went out and immediately died, and i made me feel like what i did was absolutely pointless, because when i go medic im prioritizing people with the lowest hp, then people with debuffs, then the melee mainers, then everyone else. And this is where im conflicted,do i start healing the people i know are going to be alright and arent going to die within the next 30 secs, because i feel "favortizing could be considered team trolling, but on the other hand if those seasoned veteran players are kept alive are chances of winning on h team are significantly higher, because theyll actually help the team win, its an everyday decision i find myself having to pick between 2 people who are about to die to heal, like someone as valued as Hyper at 30 hp vs some dude who started playing gmod for a week who on 22 hp, idk im just conflicted on what to do, whether to change my playstyle to see if it changes anything, but i dont want to be seen as some asshole with a medkit becuase im favoring some over others.
